{{Otheruses|other=同名學術期刊|鄉村社會學 (學術期刊)}}
'''鄉村社會學'''是[[社會學|社會學]]的分支之一，以非都市地區內的社會生活為研究範疇。更仔細來說，它是一個關於遠離人口密集地區或經濟活動地區的社會組織和行為的科學研究。正如其他社會學分支，鄉村社會學包括了統計數據檢查、[[面談|面談]]、[[社會理論|社會理論]]、觀察、調查研究和其他技巧。

與鄉村社會學相反的就是[[都市社會學|都市社會學]]。

[[農業綜合企業|農業綜合企業]]是鄉村社會學其中一個焦點，還有很多研究範疇針對農產品的經濟。其它研究包括了鄉村移民、[[人口統計學|人口統計學]]、[[環境社會學|環境社會學]]、[[休閒度假城|休閒度假城]]、公共土地政策、[[新興都市|新興都市]]、[[社會瓦解|社會瓦解]]、鄉村健康護理及教育政策。

==鄉村定義== 
社會學家定義鄉村為非市區地方。雖然美國鄉村社會學家常用美國人口調查局的定義，即人口密度低於每平方里一千人，但兩者分野仍然比較隨意。[https://web.archive.org/web/20131014182213/http://www.census.gov/geo/www/ua/ua_2k.html]2000年的人口調查報告21%美國家庭（59,274,000人）位於鄉村。[http://www.fhwa.dot.gov/planning/census/cps2k.htm] {{Wayback|url=http://www.fhwa.dot.gov/planning/census/cps2k.htm |date=20070208051446 }}
<!--
==歷史==
{{Unreferenced|date=December 2006}}

Rural sociology became prominent during the late [[industrial_revolution|industrial revolution]] in [[France|France]], [[Ireland|Ireland]], [[Prussia|Prussia]], [[Scandinavia|Scandinavia]], and the [[united_States|US]]. As urban incomes and quality of life rose, a social gap appeared between urban and rural dwellers. 

Early works of [[Max_Weber|Max Weber]] in the late [[19th_century|19th century]] has been concerned with rural sociology. In the [[1920s|1920s]], [[Edmund_deS._Brunner|Edmund deS. Brunner]] studied some 140 villages as director of the [[Institute_for_Social_and_Religious_Research|Institute for Social and Religious Research]], he reported that as [[agriculture|agriculture]] mechanized, farms were growing larger.

After [[World_War_II|World War II]], modern rural sociology began to appear in [[France|France]], [[Germany|Germany]], [[Italy|Italy]], [[the_Netherlands|the Netherlands]], and [[united_Kingdom|the UK]].

-->
==美國鄉村問題==
美國的鄉村經濟趨勢是十分複雜的，正如其他地區面對經濟下滑和[[農村人口遷出|農村人口遷出]]，而海岸及山區則面對經濟刺激與新居民流入。雖然某些地區的很多傳統鄉村工業譬如採礦業、大牧場、農業等等被新興的[[資訊科技|資訊科技]]、[[休閒度假城|休閒度假城]]、[[旅遊業|旅遊業]]、[[藝術|藝術]]所取代，但大部分已經在經濟上不可行的。這些工業為了一些地區帶來經濟增長，但一些經濟衰退地區帶來[[社會分化|社會分化]]。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.luc.edu/depts/sociology/johnson/p99webn.html |title=The Rural Rebound: Recent Nonmetropolitan Demographic Trends in the United States |accessdate=2007-02-17 |archive-date=2007-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070206210721/http://www.luc.edu/depts/sociology/johnson/p99webn.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.centerwest.org/ |title=Amercian Center for the West |accessdate=2020-09-20 |archive-date=2020-08-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200817211750/https://www.centerwest.org/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

近來，鄉村資本向市區或名為山間西部的鄉村縣、[[歐薩克|歐薩克]]、海岸地區、[[內布拉斯加州|內布拉斯加州]]的[[I-80|I-80]]縣及[[肯薩斯城市都會區|肯薩斯城市都會區]]。財富增長集中在市區、交通走廊。
<!--
Many parts of rural America are experiencing an economic slump, especially those economically dependent on agribusiness. For instance in [[1999|1999]] the prices for [[sweetcorn|sweetcorn]], [[wheat|wheat]], and [[soybeans|soybeans]] were all down approx. 33% from the [[1995|1995]]-[[1998|1998]] [[average|average]]. Food production is being subsidized by off-farm income. Some farmers are working second and third jobs to support their farms. In [[1974|1974]] 80% of farm operators were primarily farmers.  By [[1997|1997]] that had dropped to 60% (McDaniel, 2000), (Lee, 2000).

Some natural resource-based industries within rural areas are experiencing [[resource_depletion|resource depletion]], whereas other rural areas in states such as [[Wyoming|Wyoming]], [[Colorado|Colorado]], and [[New_Mexico|New Mexico]] are seeing huge economic growth due to the extraction of [[natural_gas|natural gas]] and other minerals. 

Rural society is faced with various problems including the environmental degradation and overuse of water resources, the establishment and inadequate regulation of [[toxic_waste|toxic waste]] dumps, and [[poverty|poverty]]. The loss of rural population to urban areas is also an area of concern, especially in northern states, such as [[North_Dakota|North Dakota]].
-->
